# Commit message version tags

Every commit on `main` must start with a sequential version tag: `vN: short description`.

Rules:
- Use the next integer after the latest commit on `main` (check with `git log -1 --oneline`)
- Format: `v41: what changed` — lowercase after the colon, no duplicate version numbers
- Never reuse or skip numbers; never commit without a `vN:` prefix
- Release-note-only commits follow the same rule (e.g. `v42: update release notes for …`)

Examples:
- `v42: default GUI to Russian and hide secondary subsystems`
- `v43: updated readme`

Bad:
- `updated readme` (missing prefix)
- `v0: update release notes` when latest is v35 (wrong number)
- `v39: …` when v39 already exists (duplicate)
